snippet.textDisplay: This is going to be complicated, so I'm very sorry for that. But I'm a cancer survivor who only has 9 teeth left in my mouth for the time being, they will be removed thanks to radiation and I haven't eaten a solid meal in nearly 3 years, I went from !90 to 129 pounds, please do the math on your end as I'm nearly starving to death for the weights. I had a great recipe for more than a year, but it's now too thick as I only have one type of saliva glands after the radiation so it has to be as thin as milk. The thin saliva glands are dead thanks to the radiation (who freakin' knew that was a thing???) Otherwise it chokes me out. I always love your flavor profiles and yet I didn't discover you until the  cancer because life was too busy for me then. The only thing my mouth can't handle now is capsaicin, acidic, thick or too basic. it's like setting off explosions in my mouth these days. Thank you if you can and I'll be sure to pass them on to other support groups for those with my situation. If not, not one second of pressure, I get no help from anywhere, I just figure as I can't survive on Strawberry or Choco milk for too much longer. If you can help, so much thanks for you, if you can't absolutely no hard feelings. All you guys are the best! I've turned all my loved ones and friends onto your website. Never stop what you do!

snippet.textDisplay:
“No one under the age of 50 has bought (citrus jam) for themselves”
I have. I buy it all the time. It’s delicious, especially the spicy ones. Also, “marmalade” is quince jam, exclusively. Orange jam is, well, orange jam. “Marmalade” comes from the portuguese word “marmelada”, “quince” is “marmelo”.
